{
  "texts": [
    "The original algorithm learns from preference judgments, requiring access to chosen and rejected responses in the (x, y w, y l) format.",
    "Since our dataset contains gold and corrupted instructions instead, we modify ORPO so that the algorithm accepts (x w, x l, y).",
    "We refer to this modified method as Instructional Odds Ratio Preference Optimization (I-ORPO), where the modified loss is calculated as:",
    "In the original ORPO formulation, the model is learning if the log probability of P θ (y w |x), denoted logps(y w |x), increases and log probability of P θ (y l |x), denoted logps(y l |x w), decreases after a number of training steps, resulting in the log odds ratio increasing.",
    "In I-ORPO, the same y is used for both instruction types."
  ]
}